schema.name: material
schema.title: Material
schema.description: Material to expose clear coat properties.

schema.name: clearCoatMap
schema.title: CC Map
schema.description: Monochrome clear coat intensity map (default is null). If specified, will be multiplied by normalized clearCoat value and/or vertex colors.

schema.name: clearCoatMapChannel
schema.title: CC Map Channel
schema.description: Color channel of the clear coat intensity map to use. Can be "r", "g", "b" or "a".

schema.name: clearCoatMapOffset
schema.title: CC Map Offset
schema.description: Controls the 2D offset of the clear coat intensity map. Each component is between 0 and 1.

schema.name: clearCoatMapTiling
schema.title: CC Map Tiling
schema.description: Controls the 2D tiling of the clear coat intensity map.

schema.name: clearCoatMapUv
schema.title: CC Map UV
schema.description: Clear coat intensity map UV channel.

schema.name: clearCoatVertexColor
schema.title: CC Vertex Color
schema.description: Use mesh vertex colors for clear coat intensity. If clearCoatMap is set, it will be multiplied by vertex colors.

schema.name: clearCoatVertexColorChannel
schema.title: CC Vertex Color Channel
schema.description: Vertex color channel to use for clear coat intensity. Can be "r", "g", "b" or "a".

schema.name: clearCoat
schema.title: CC Intensity
schema.description: Defines intensity of clear coat layer from 0 to 1. Clear coat layer is disabled when clearCoat == 0. Default value is 0.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMap
schema.title: CC Gloss Map
schema.description: Monochrome clear coat glossiness map (default is null). If specified, will be multiplied by normalized clearCoatGlossiness value and/or vertex colors.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapChannel
schema.title: CC Gloss Map Channel
schema.description: Color channel of the clear coat gloss map to use. Can be "r", "g", "b" or "a".

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapOffset
schema.title: CC Gloss Map Offset
schema.description: Controls the 2D offset of the clear coat gloss map. Each component is between 0 and 1.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapTiling
schema.title: CC Gloss Map Tiling
schema.description: Controls the 2D offset of the clear coat gloss map. Each component is between 0 and 1.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapUv
schema.title: CC Gloss Map UV
schema.description: Clear coat gloss map UV channel.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapVertexColor
schema.title: CC Gloss Map Vertex Color
schema.description: Use mesh vertex colors for clear coat glossiness. If clearCoatGlossMap is set, it will be multiplied by vertex colors.

schema.name: clearCoatGlossMapVertexColorChannel
schema.title: CC Gloss Map Vertex Color Channel
schema.description: Vertex color channel to use for clear coat glossiness. Can be "r", "g", "b" or "a".

schema.name: clearCoatGlossiness
schema.title: CC Glossiness
schema.description: Defines the clear coat glossiness of the clear coat layer from 0 (rough) to 1 (mirror).

schema.name: clearCoatNormalMap
schema.title: CC Normal Map
schema.description: The clear coat normal map of the material (default is null). The texture must contains normalized, tangent space normals.

schema.name: clearCoatNormalMapOffset
schema.title: CC Normal Map Offset
schema.description: Controls the 2D offset of the main clear coat normal map. Each component is between 0 and 1.

schema.name: clearCoatNormalMapTiling
schema.title: CC Normal Map Tiling
schema.description: Controls the 2D tiling of the main clear coat normal map.

schema.name: clearCoatNormalMapUv
schema.title: CC Normal Map UV
schema.description: Clear coat normal map UV channel.

schema.name: clearCoatBumpiness
schema.title: CC Bumpiness
schema.description: The bumpiness of the clear coat layer. This value scales the assigned main clear coat normal map. It should be normally between 0 (no bump mapping) and 1 (full bump mapping), but can be set to e.g. 2 to give even more pronounced bump effect.
